Package testHelp

The testHelp library consists of a single package testHelp which includes four groups of Java classes and interfaces.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FunctionNormalizers
    One of two interfaces - the other is UnboundMethodNormalizers - with no abstract methods that bundle static methods which normalize specialized functions and unbound methods which take arguments and/or return values of primitive types (boolean, double, int, long) to generic functions and methods which take arguments and return values of the corresponding object types (Boolean, Double, Integer, Long).
    NormalizedFunctionCallers
    This interface with no abstract or default methods that bundles a set of static methods which call normalized functions (including static methods and bound instance methods as well as non-class functions defined by lambda expressions) with the number of args appropriate to the normalized function, and either retur a value or fail depending on the expectation as to whether the call will return normally or throw an exception.
    NormalizedUnboundMethodCallers
    This interface with no abstract or default methods that bundles a set of static methods which call normalized unbound methods (non-static methods that are not bound to an object of their class) with an object of the their class as first argument plus the number of args appropriate to the normalized unbound method, and either return a value or fail depending on the expectation as to whether the call will return normally or throw an exception.
    SupplementaryFunctionalInterfaces
    An interface with no abstract or default methods that bundles functional interfaces not in the standard Java 8 set but named in the style of the standard set.
    SupplementaryFunctionalInterfaces.TriConsumer<T,U,V>
    Superinterface of UnboundMethodInterfaces.BiConsumerUnboundMethod
    SupplementaryFunctionalInterfaces.TriFunction<T,U,V,R>
    Superinterface of UnboundMethodInterfaces.BiFunctionUnboundMethod
    SupplementaryFunctionalInterfaces.TriPredicate<T,U,V>
    Superinterface of UnboundMethodInterfaces.BiPredicateUnboundMethod
    UnboundMethodInterfaces
    An interface with no abstract or default methods that bundles a set of unbound method interfaces that parallels the standard Java set of functional interfaces.

    UnboundMethodNormalizers
    One of two interfaces - the other is FunctionNormalizers - with no abstract methods that bundle static methods which normalize specialized functions and unbound methods which take arguments and/or return values of primitive types (boolean, double, int, long) to generic functions and methods which take arguments and return values of the corresponding object types (Boolean, Double, Integer, Long).
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods
    An interface with no abstract or default methods that bundles "voidable" VFunction and VUnboundMethod interfaces and static methods that convert fully typed to "voidable" functional and unbound method types.
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VBiFunction<A1,A2,R>
    A "voidable" functional interface which takes two args of any generic types <A1,A2> and returns a value of any generic type <R> including VoidR.
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VBiUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2,R>
    A "voidable" unbound methoid interface which takes, in addtional to an initial class instance argument, two arguments of any generic types <A1,A2> and returns a value of any generic type <R> including VoidR.
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VFunction<A,R>
    A "voidable" functional interface which takes no arg or a single arg which may be of any generic type <A> including VoidA and returns a value of any generic type <R> including VoidR.
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VTriFunction<A1,A2,A3,R>
    A "voidable" functional interface which takes three args any generic types <A1,A2,A3> and returns a value of any generic type <R> including VoidR.
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VUnboundMethod<C,A,R>
    A "voidable" unbound method interface which takes, after an initial class instance arg, no arg or a single arg which may be of any generic type <A> including VoidA and returns a value of any generic type <R> including VoidR.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AssertionTools
    An internal class that bundles a set of tools that are used in the various assertion classes and can be called directly from test code.
    BooleanAssertion
    Represents an assertion about a boolean variable.
    CallableAssertion
    Represents an assertion about a snippet of code (functional object that implements the standard Java Callable interface) that returns some value.
    CollectionAssertion<T>
    Represents an assertion about a collection, like an array or ArrayList.
    ConsoleTester
    Simplifies testing of a Java application with a main method that reads input from System.in and/or writes output to System.out through getOutput and related methods.
    DelegatingInputStream
    A derivative of InputStream which delegates to an internally stored reference to a "real" InputStream which can be changed.
    DelegatingPrintStream
    A derivative of PrintStream which delegates to an internally stored reference to a "real" PrintStream which can be changed.
    DoubleAssertion
    Represents an assertion about a double value
    EnumAssertion<EnumType>
    Represents an assertion about an enum value of a given enum type
    ErrorOutputChunker
    This class bundles a collection of static types and methods for parsing text that may contain one or more exception stacktraces and/or non-stacktrace content into chunks.
    ExceptionAssertion
    Represents an assertion about an Exception
    ExecutableAssertion
    Represents an assertion about some executable piece of code (Callable or Runnable, in Java terms).
    FractionAssertion
    Represents an assertion related to a Fraction.
    FractionAssertion.Fraction  
    GenericExceptionAssertion<T extends Throwable>
    Generic exception assertion class.
    GenericObjectAssertion<T>
    Generic object assertion class, for use where the assertion methods defined in GenericObjectAssertionBase are sufficient.
    GenericObjectAssertionBase<T,AssertionT>
    Abstract base class for assertion classes for object (as opposed to primitive) types.
    IntAssertion
    Represents an assertion about an integer.
    ObjectAssertion
    Represents an assertion about an object
    OutputInfo
    An internal (package-private) class which holds data accumulated and used in ConsoleTester.getOutput and Assertion classes and provides methods for printing the data.
    OutputInfo.TestNameInfo
    Information on the current test in the test file being run.
    RunnableAssertion
    Represents an assertion about a runnable snippet of code, with no return value.
    StringAssertion
    Represents an assertion about a String
    verify
    A collection of static methods to verify assertions in tests.
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VoidA
    Class of void argument (possible in C and C++ function/method declarations though not in Java).
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VoidR
    Class of void return value (a standard feature of C, C++ and Java function/method declarations).

Package testHelp Description

The testHelp library consists of a single package testHelp which includes four groups of Java classes and interfaces.

(1) OUTPUT (capture output printed to System.out and System.err)

Original, refactored and extended

  • ConsoleTester

Extensions

  • DelegatingInputStream
  • DelegatingPrintStream
  • ErrorOutputChunker
  • OutputInfo

Unittest

  • ConsoleTesterTests
  • ConsoleTesterVFunctionAndVUnboundMethodTests
  • MiscTests
  • SampleOutputInfoPrintingTests

(2) ASSERTIONS (all called directly or indirectly through fluent verify interface)

Original

  • BooleanAssertion
  • CallableAssertion
  • CollectionAssertion
  • CompareType
  • DoubleAssertion
  • ExceptionAssertion
  • ExecutableAssertion
  • FractionAssertion
  • IntAssertion
  • ObjectAssertion
  • RunnableAssertion
  • StringAssertion
  • verify

Extensions

  • AssertionTools
  • EnumAssertion
  • GenericExceptionAssertion
  • GenericObjectAssertion
  • GenericObjectAssertionBase
  • NumericCompareType

Unittest

  • GenericAssertionTests

(3) FUNCTIONAL OBJECTS (lambda expressions, member references and other implementations of functional interfaces) - all extensions

  • FunctionNormalizers
  • NormalizedFunctionCallers
  • NormalizedUnboundMethodCallers
  • SupplementaryFunctionalInterfaces
  • UnboundMethodInterfaces
  • UnboundMethodNormalizers
  • VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods

Unittests

  • FunctionAndUnboundMethodCallerSpecializedTests
  • FunctionAndUnboundMethodCallerTests
  • MethodReferenceToFunctionalTypeAssignments
  • TestClassWithNormalizedMethods
  • TestClassWithSpecializedMethods
  • VFunctionAndVUnboundMethodTests

(4) EXCEPTIONS - all extensions

  • TestHelpError
  • WrappedException
